Windows Forensics Tools (Acquisition & Analysis)

Registry Acquisition & Analysis Tools

KAPE (Kroll Artifact Parser and Extractor)
	•	Purpose: Live data acquisition and triage  
	•	Use: Collect registry hives and forensic artifacts from live systems  
	•	Features:
	•	Fast targeted collection  
	•	CLI and GUI support  
	•	Useful for incident response  

FTK Imager
	•	Purpose: Data acquisition and file extraction  
	•	Use: Mount disk images or extract files from live systems  
	•	Features:
	•	Mount and browse disk images  
	•	Export registry hives and files  
	•	“Obtain Protected Files” for live systems  
	•	Limitation: Does not extract Amcache.hve  

Registry Viewer (AccessData)
	•	Purpose: View registry hives  
	•	Use: Analyze extracted registry files  
	•	Features:
	•	Simple UI (similar to regedit)  
	•	Single hive loading  
	•	Limitation: No transaction log support  

Registry Explorer (Eric Zimmerman)
	•	Purpose: Advanced registry analysis  
	•	Use: Analyze multiple hives with higher accuracy  
	•	Features:
	•	Loads multiple hives  
	•	Incorporates transaction logs  
	•	Bookmark feature for key artifacts  

RegRipper
	•	Purpose: Automated registry parsing  
	•	Use: Extract forensic data from registry hives  
	•	Features:
	•	Generates structured reports  
	•	CLI and GUI support  
	•	Limitation: No transaction log support  

