File System & Data Recovery Tools

Autopsy
	•	Purpose: Disk image analysis and recovery  
	•	Use: Analyze disk images, recover deleted files, parse artifacts  
	•	Features:
	•	GUI-based forensic suite  
	•	Supports multiple data sources  
	•	Parses browser history and system artifacts  

MFTECmd (Eric Zimmerman)
	•	Purpose: NTFS artifact parsing  
	•	Use: Parse $MFT, $Boot, and $UsnJrnl  
	•	Features:
	•	Outputs CSV/JSON  
	•	Extracts file metadata and timestamps  
	•	CLI-based  

EZViewer (Eric Zimmerman)
	•	Purpose: Visualization tool  
	•	Use: View output from EZ tools (CSV data)  
	•	Features:
	•	Clean interface  
	•	Simplifies analysis  

Hex Editors (Generic)
	•	Purpose: Raw data inspection  
	•	Use: Analyze binary data and recover file signatures  
	•	Features:
	•	View hex/binary data  
	•	Manual file carving support  

Disk Imaging Tools

	•	Purpose: Create forensic disk images  
	•	Use: Bit-by-bit copy of storage devices  
	•	Examples:
	•	FTK Imager  
	•	dd (Linux)  
	•	Features:
	•	Preserves original evidence  
	•	Enables offline analysis  

