Execution & User Activity Artifact Tools

PECmd (Eric Zimmerman)
	•	Purpose: Parse Windows Prefetch files  
	•	Use: Extract execution evidence from .pf files  
	•	Features:
	•	Shows run count and last execution  
	•	Supports directory parsing  
	•	Outputs CSV/JSON  

WxTCmd (Eric Zimmerman)
	•	Purpose: Parse Windows Timeline  
	•	Use: Extract user activity from ActivitiesCache.db  
	•	Features:
	•	SQLite parsing  
	•	Outputs CSV  
	•	Shows app usage and duration  

JLECmd (Eric Zimmerman)
	•	Purpose: Parse Jump Lists  
	•	Use: Extract recent file and application usage  
	•	Features:
	•	Supports multiple formats  
	•	Outputs CSV/JSON/HTML  
	•	Provides execution timestamps  

LECmd (Eric Zimmerman)
	•	Purpose: Parse shortcut (.lnk) files  
	•	Use: Extract file access and execution data  
	•	Features:
	•	Shows file paths and timestamps  
	•	Supports directory parsing  
	•	Outputs CSV/JSON/XML  

WebCache Analysis Tools

	•	Purpose: Parse IE/Edge WebCache database  
	•	Use: Extract browsing and local file access history  
	•	Examples:
	•	Autopsy  
	•	ESE database parsers  

---

Notes

	•	Use dedicated tools instead of native Windows tools for forensic accuracy  
	•	Combine multiple artifacts/tools for reliable conclusions  
	•	Prefer offline analysis on acquired images over live systems


